  "development_type": "Certificates of Lawful Development",
  "description": "APPLICATION FOR A LAWFUL DEVELOPMENT CERTIFICATE IN RESPECT OF THE PROPOSED ERECTION OF HIP TO GABLE AND REAR DORMER ROOF EXTENSION AND INSERTION OF X2 ROOFLIGHTS TO FRONT ROOFSLOPE",
  "site_name": null,
  "decision_conditions": [
    "Reason : 1 - This proposal CONSTITUTES DEVELOPMENT within the meaning of Section 55 of the Town and Country Planning Act 1990, and a planning application IS REQUIRED. \r\n\r\nBy reason of absence of sufficient and consistent drawings to satisfactorily demonstrate that the proposed roof extensions including rear roof extension and hip to gable extension would not exceed 50 cubic metres, the proposal thereby fails to comply with Class B. B.1 (d)(ii) of Schedule 2, Part 1, of the Town & Country Planning (General Permitted Development) (England) Order 2015. Planning permission would therefore be required.\r\n",
    "Reason : 2 - This proposal CONSTITUTES DEVELOPMENT within the meaning of Section 55 of the Town and Country Planning Act 1990, and a planning application IS REQUIRED.\r\n \r\nBy reason of absence of sufficient and consistent drawings to satisfactorily demonstrate that the proposed rear roof extension would be setback from the eaves by at least 0.2m when measured along the roof slope from the outside edge of the eaves, the proposal thereby fails to comply with Class B. B.2 (b)(i)(bb) of Schedule 2, Part 1, of the Town & Country Planning (General Permitted Development) (England) Order 2015. Planning permission would therefore be required.\r\n"
